description.1: The Fantastic Four are whisked back in time to the year 1936! And a young Nick Fury is threatening to kill Hitler! But at the opportune moment?
description.2: When Kitty Pryde is ambushed by the Freedom Force, the X-Men intervene to save their young teammate!
description.6: Guest-starring the Man Without Fear! After uncovering Daredevil's secret identity, the Kingpin makes Matt Murdock's life a living hell. Spider-Man vs. Wilson Fisk! Plus, a young girl is saved from kidnappers in the midst of a blizzard.
description.7: Captain Marvel, Namor, and Captain America investigate the disappearance of their teammates. From the beginning, however, Captain America suspects Kang. The rest of the team makes it to Limbo, but will it be too late for kidnapped members Wasp, Black Knight and Hercules?
description.8: Blue Streak breaks out! Plus: Find out what happens to Princess Python when the Serpent Society revokes her membership!
description.9: Ikaris versus Thena! Following this issue, who will lead the Eternals?
description.10: The Enchantress casts her spell over Vision...and Wanda's not having it. A battle between two witches for the heart of one synthetic man!
description.12: The fiery climax! Firestar's reached her full power, and learned about Emma Frost's plot against her!
description.16: Welcome to the Massachusetts Academy, New Mutants! Hope you survive the experience! The team confronts Emma Frost and her Hellions on their home turf. Magneto realizes he’s been played for a fool all too late.
description.17: No longer a frog, Thor returns to Asgard in his true form. Meanwhile, Kurse arrives with a terrible blood thirst! Someone will die in this issue!
description.21: The West Coast Avengers meet up with their old ally Firebird once again, but this time she's not alone!
description.23: Power Man guest-stars! Quicksilver, Scarlet Witch and Vision join the Harlem hero for a demon bust. Crystal's fling with Norm Webster heats up.
description.25: Emma Frost's sinister claws sink deeper into Firestar's mind! Now, it's only a matter of time before Angelica Jones becomes the Hellfire Club's deadliest assassin!
description.26: In this jam-packed finale, The Punisher must fight against the odds to eliminate The Trust once and for all.
description.28: The Hobgoblin unmasked! In the heat of battle, Spider-Man discovers that his deadly foe isn't a foe after all. The Fly makes his escape!
description.29: Kang has almost eliminated all the time divergent duplicates created each time he jumped through time. Meanwhile, the public protests Namor's membership with the Avengers. The Wasp, Black Knight and Hercules are transported to Limbo by Kang where he hopes they will help him destroy the final time duplicate.
description.30: What's Cap doing with Hawkeye's weapons? And what is Hawkeye doing with Cap's shield?
description.34: While Matt is being nursed back to help by Sister Maggie, he discovers a secret about her that will change their relationship forever! Meanwhile, Kingpin commissions a Daredevil costume...
description.35: Speak now or forever hold your peace! When an unwanted guest crashes Bruce and Betty's wedding, Rick Jones intervenes. Will this interloper ruin the newlywed's big day?
description.36: While Tony Stark launches his first commercial Space Shuttle, the now, evil Goliath escapes the W.C. Avengers compound and takes his revenge!
description.40: Reed Richards must follow Annihilus back to Earth to stop a Baluurian invasion- a true life or death scenario. Will the rest of our heroes go on without their courageous leader?
description.42: Who has captured whom on Zeltros? That's what everyone wants to know when three different civilizations invade that world! It's up to Luke Skywalker and the Hoojibs to save the day. If that weren't enough, Luke meets the villainous Toffs [sic] for the first time!
description.43: The Time-Matrix-Alternating Stabilizer throws Spider-Ham and the interns back to London during World War II!
description.44: Misty's feelings about Danny become bitterly entangled in an emotional web that threatens to ruin her life! Meanwhile, Power Man and Iron Fist find themselves in the ultimate peril when they confront the brother of the Dragon King!
description.46: Sersi is throwing a bash, and you’re invited! Can this fun-loving Eternal still play host when a crew of party crashers wreak havoc?
description.47: Ultron-12 wants to make peace with his "father," Hank Pym! But Ultron-11 is still around - and he's got decidedly different intentions!
description.49: The New Mutants all share a dream that portends their untimely deaths! Emma Frost appeals to Magneto with an unusual offer.
description.50: Frog Thor has returned to the shining realm of Asgard and sets out to confront Loki. Prepare for a battle between frog and god!
description.52: Ben is warned off of investigating a story about Murdock and the Kingpin. A wounded Matt is tended by Sister Maggie.
description.53: Love is in the air for Bruce and Betty! Meanwhile, the battle rages on between the Hulkbusters and Doc Samson. The worst outcome imaginable comes to pass.
description.54: Tony Stark launches his brand-new business venture unaware that A.I.M. is lurking in the background ready to squelch it before it gets off the ground! And they've got the greatest super-weapon since the birth (or death) of Modok!
description.58: The destruction of the Baxter Building has caused an unusual mass to hover over Earth! Meanwhile, Blastaar has captured Reed in the Negative Zone!
description.59: Nightcrawler gets caught up in Arcade's machinations. Is this a new swashbuckling adventure for the teleporting mutant? Or a one-way ticket to his doom?
description.61: What is the true nature of Thena and Kro’s relationship? Plus, the Deviant priests reveal ancient secrets about the fate of their people!
description.62: The Hobgoblin returns! Peter Parker gives up being Spider-Man! And Mary Jane won't stand for it!
description.63: Silver Surfer joins the battle against the Beyonder in the Rocky Mountains! But when the Surfer realizes that this battle threatens the cosmic balance, the Avengers must improvise a new plan to save the planet.
description.64: The Armadillo is about to give up a promising career as an Unlimited Class Wrestler, due to devastating personal problems. Can Cap help? Plus: A dramatic turning point in the relationship between Steve Rogers and Bernie Rosenthal.
description.67: While Crystal and Scarlet Witch prepare for the holidays, Vizh unravels the mystery of the A.I. Brotherhood of Mutants.
description.69: Firestar's beginnings as a mutant, trained by...the White Queen!? Will the X-Men be able to get through to her before she becomes another one of Emma Frost's deadly agents?
description.70: After cutting ties with The Trust, Punisher must now defend himself against their mindless clones!
description.73: Mirage must reconcile with the frightening new abilities bestowed upon her by the Valkyrie.
description.74: Far beneath the streets of New York City exists a series of mysterious tunnels where things are not always what they seem. For example, a frog who is really the Asgardian god of thunder...
description.77: The cat side of Tigra is taking over! The only way the West Coast Avengers can save her is to journey to the dimension of the Cat People! But will they be greeted as welcomed guests...or attacked as hated invaders?
description.79: Vision and Wanda's closest kin gather for Thanksgiving dinner. But this family affair is soon cut short- by the Brotherhood of Evil Mutants?
description.81: What is a god? Beyonder poses this question and more in the jaw-dropping conclusion to Secret Wars II. Will reality be ripped to shreds as the entire Marvel Universe takes on the One from Beyond? The answer's more complicated than you think!
description.82: The origin of Marvel's most fiery mutant! Angelica Jones is just a normal girl - until she starts developing strange powers! Now, with the X-Men, the New Mutants, and the White Queen all after her, what's this new mutant to do?
description.84: The Trust deploys Punisher doppelgangers to con and kill mobsters. Can Castle trust anyone in this game?
description.88: A Secret Wars II tie-in. The Beyonder battles Mephisto for the soul of the Spider!
description.89: Captain America's suspicions about the Beyonder prove accurate, when he is held prisoner by the villain in a mountain cave. Tossed into the Beyonder's energy tornado, Captain Marvel, Black Knight, Namor, and Hercules attempt to collect their bearings and find Cap before it's too late! The Beyonder promises to unleash his fury against the Avengers!
description.90: Cap is trapped by the Porcupine! At least that's what the Serpent Society thinks, because that's what the Porcupine wants them to know! If the Porcupine succeeds, his life of crime is over! If he fails ...
description.91: The Master Conniver has a few tricks up his sleeve that throws Spider-Ham off the trail! Plus, vegetables that wield guns! 'Nuff said!
description.92: The mighty Beyonder has come to New York! Can Power Man and Iron Fist help him understand the people of Earth before it's too late?!
description.94: The Eternals face treason from within as one of their most trusted members compromises their path to victory. The day belongs to the Deviants!
description.95: Matt Murdock's life continues to unravel and he decides to confront the Kingpin directly.
description.96: Things are turning around for Bruce Banner! Free from the grip of his alter ego, Bruce becomes the leader of the Hulkbusters...and asks Betty Ross a very important question!
description.97: Madame Masque is taking names, but why is Bethany Cabe on her list? And why is Madame Masque in Bethany's body? Tony must rely on the aid of a mute A.I.M scientist to return each woman to her orginal corporeal form.

4.text: What does it mean for the droids when a high powered laser enters the picture?

5.text: The Power Pack kids are held hostage in Snarkworld along with Kofi and his father!

11.text: The Thing continues to struggle with sudden bouts of dizziness until he undergoes yet another mutation. Guest-starring She-Hulk!

13.text: Dakota North is enlisted to protect a fashion designer from someone who is trying to sabotage his new release.

15.text: Top Dog goes missing…and when he's found, he's on the television as the star of a commercial!

20.text: Balder triumphant! With the Frost Giants defeated and his love freed from their clutches, Balder sets out for Asgrad for a date with destiny...

21.text: The West Coast Avengers meet up with their old ally Firebird once again, but this time she's not alone!

22.text: The showdown no fan can miss! Tyndall of Klarn reclaims his place in Weirdworld with his final battle against Lord Raven. Will elves Velanna and Tyndall at long last be free of Raven’s dark sorcery?

24.text: The Power Broker cuts a deal with Sharon Ventura! One that leaves her powered up and in dire need of help...

31.text: The Ewoks run up against the might of the Mountain Spirit!

32.text: Alex uses his powers to save his crush Allison McCourt from a bully.

33.text: With Mayhem’s assist, Cloak and Dagger prevent a heroin ring from infiltrating the city.

37.text: Tom Thumb has been diagnosed with cancer. The cure lies in the hands of the Scarlet Centurion! Plus, Nighthawk begins his recruitment process for a Squadron Supreme counter-strike force!

47.text: Ultron-12 wants to make peace with his "father," Hank Pym! But Ultron-11 is still around - and he's got decidedly different intentions!

48.text: Iuriale is intent on ensnaring Strange with her siren’s song! But will the good Doctor take the bait? Self-control is tested, as Doc Strange takes on a Medusa-like seductress.

49.text: The New Mutants all share a dream that portends their untimely deaths! Emma Frost appeals to Magneto with an unusual offer.

51.text: Carl Maddicks is conducting mutant-reversing experiments on the Beast in an attempt to reverse the mutation of his own son!

55.text: The Whizzer faces off against Bollix and the Rustler! Can the Whizzer defeat two of his personal enemies when they wear Tom Thumb's force-field belts?

66.text: In this special issue, Top Dog meets Royal Roy!

68.text: The return of the Puppet Master. And his reemergence may spell disaster for Ben Grimm and Alicia! But then, a surprising twist...

71.text: R2-D2 and C-3PO are sent by the Intergalactic Droid Agency to the tiny planet Dodz to serve their new master, crystal merchant Lott Kemp. But when the droids arrive on Dodz they discover that Kemp has gone missing and his home has been destroyed, thus a new adventure begins!

72.text: Katie and Jack are forced to reveal their identities while saving their favorite author from the will of thugs!

73.text: Mirage must reconcile with the frightening new abilities bestowed upon her by the Valkyrie.

75.text: Hank’s reunion with his ex-girlfriend is violently interrupted by the size changing Tower!

76.text: Captured by the Frost Giant's king, Utgard-Loki, Balder is forced into mortal combat in monarch's personal arena against an enemy wielding none other than the mystical Sword of Frey!

77.text: The cat side of Tigra is taking over! The only way the West Coast Avengers can save her is to journey to the dimension of the Cat People! But will they be greeted as welcomed guests...or attacked as hated invaders?

78.text: Tyndall, Velanna, and Mud-Butt are in a hotbed of danger…and the domain of villainous Lord Raven! Will young Tyndall finally come face-to-face with his greatest adversary? And if he does, will his companions give Tyndall the assist he needs?

80.text: It’s “Ladies Night” as the women call the shots in the wrestling ring! Guest-starring Sharon Ventura and the super-strong Titania.

83.text: Beast comes to Alison with an offer to join a new X-Team! Don't miss the this action-packed final issue!

85.text: When the Ice Demon possesses Wicket, it may spell terrible things for the Ewoks.

86.text: Katie is kidnapped by demons as a pawn for a spell that will bring New York City into Limbo!

87.text: Cloak and Dagger unknowingly help create a superhuman who is not only extraordinarily powerful, but very vengeful. Introducing Mayhem!

98.text: Nighthawk has been captured by Master Menace! But things are not as they seem and when Nighthawk reveals his true intentions to Master Menace, the pieces begin to fall in place. Are the Redeemers planning on taking down the Squadron Supreme?
